An image of her is the only thing keeping me living 

Here I stand in a room with a picture of beloved, Clare on the wall 
ahead of me, with her writing on the wall around the painting. She 
was a wonderful woman, a charming women who got her way. Her love 
was unconditional, a love that would fix wars for generations. That's 
why to this day why she loved me and not some other man. She died a few
years ago from a car crash while protecting me from the major damage that
could have been casued to my body. That's how pure her heart was not even 
death stood in the way of her love. Before she died, she had blood cancer 
which she would have died a week after the crash happened. So she hid a room
from me, she hung a picture of her knowing I would miss her, and she wrote things,
like stories and the things liked most about me, she did all of this while I was
at work. Her stories amazed me and the compliments flattered me. If she was still alive 
to this day I wonder want would happen, wpould my life be different? It probably would be.
I wonder if she would still be proud of me. I used to come home from work every day with some
flowers in my hand, she cried tears every time I gave her the flowers. So long and stil haven't 
forgotten the memories we made together in the past. You can never escape the past, no matter how
hard you try.